Running a VAR in R

Dr.Â Croushore

Mar 6, 2021

R Markdown

This R program can be used interactively to run a VAR in R. Read the data set and load the library âvarsâ.

library(readxl)
sims <- read_excel("/home/andrew/Documents/timeseries/VAR/sims3data.xls")
View(sims)
library(vars)
## Loading required package: MASS

Now, organize the data as a time series. The data we want (logs of GDP, M2, and P) are in columns 6 to 8.

x <- sims[,6:8]
y <- ts(data = x, start = c(1959,1), frequency = 4, end = c(2020,4)) # data start in 1959Q1 and end in 2020Q4.
#y

Run the VAR. The p=4 part says to use 4 lags of all variables in each equation.

var1 <- VAR(y, p=4) 
summary(var1)

Use the âirfâ command to show the impies. I took them out 10 years to see them clearly (10 years x 4 quarters per year = 40 quarters).

impies <- irf(var1, n.ahead=40)
plot(impies)

To forecast from a VAR, use the âpredictâ command.

fcst1 <- predict(var1, n.ahead = 40)
plot(fcst1)
